le> Where to find this mob?</span><hr size=1> I decided to start the Warden of Tunare quest. It begins gaining the Initiate of Tunare rank which requires four sets of skeleton bones, no problem at all, and four ghast hearts. The ghasts are supposedly in LF but I ran through the zone a couple of times today using tracking and wolf form and only saw one raccous ghast - easy kill, no heart. No other ghasts ever appeared on tracking.  All in all, I spent about an hour roaming throught the zone to no avail. Just bad luck?<br>
<br>
Has anyone started this quest and found ghasts, if so, approximately where were they - which quadrant of the zone NE, SE, NW,SW? Also never saw the next two mobs required for the next step, a courier and a necromancer.<br>
<br>
--Eloria Rivermist<br>
lvl 32 Soldier of Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rtfm>rtfm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/01 3:06:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Not bad luck.</span><hr size=1> Ok, the gold rush is mostly over, so I will spill what beans I have on these.<br>
<br>
The Ghasts spawn only at EQ night and they will despawn around 8 am if no one kills them.<br>
<br>
Their PH's are *not* the stationary undead at the shrine.<br>
<br>
They are the wandering undead-&gt;skellies&lt;- and mummies- east and west of the shrine.<br>
<br>
I think the most I ever saw spawn during one EQ night was 6.  And that was with me and another druid slamming the heck out of the ph's.  And they run about 1 in 4 that have a heart.<br>
<br>
The necro and the courier seem to be broke because of the frightlings quest and the take over of LF.   They will too spawn at night, and iirc, when I first did this, about every third EQ night would come up on track.<br>
<br>
It takes some time, but well worth the effort.  Have wolf up, so you don't agro the brownies.<br>
<br>
The necro spawns right at the shrine, casts a feeble pet.  When he dies about 5 minutes later, the courier spawns and runs to the DE camp and stands there next to the Princess.  She will own you(600ish dd iiirc), so get the courier before he gets there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueloriar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EloriaR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/01 7:37:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not bad luck (or thanks rtfm)</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the tip, I was there during an EQ night but never thought about the skellies or mummies being place holders. I spent my time looking for ghasts. I'll get my druid buddy to go with me, also in wolf form, and we will declare war on the skellies/mummies .<br>
<br>
Thanks again rtfm.<br>
<br>
--Eloria Rivermist<br>
lvl 33 Soldier of Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/01 10:17:16 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/images/vermsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not bad luck (or thanks rtfm)</span><hr size=1> Or just use harmony if she gets to the Princess. <p><p><font face="Tahoma" size="1">Ligge - Fennin Ro<br><a href="http://www.eqguide.com">www.eqguide.com</a><br>
Changing Tide CoGuild Leader<br><b>
"You must be the change you wish to see in the world." - Mahatma Ghandi</b><br>"Never argue with an idiot. They drag you down to their level then beat you with experience."  Unknown</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rtfm>rtfm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/20/01 12:31:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not bad luck (or thanks rtfm)</span><hr size=1> Fair enough.<br>
<br>
The first time I saw the courier it was standing right next to the princess.    I watched as another druid harmonied them, tried to pull the courier, got the princess.  Then I watched them both chase the druid to the zone.  He did not make it, and she turned her attention to me.  I figured that they were just too close to be separately pulled.<br>
<br>
I figured it would be easier all around to get the courier before it gets to camp, and was.<br>
<br>
Were you able to harmony pull the courier without the princess, Ligge? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugrummel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grummel</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/26/01 5:18:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not bad luck (or thanks rtfm)</span><hr size=1> Just a little hint for the courier:<br>
<br>
Bind at steamfontzone and spawn the courier. Immediatley gate (to the steamfont zone) There the courier will spawn and you get him far before the DE camp. <p><font size=+2>Grummel</font><br>
<font size=+1>Testserver Druid</font><br>
Enjoying EQ everytime and everyplace.</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showMessage?topicID=3020.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showMessage?topicID=3025.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.emailToFriend?topicID=3011.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.threadControl?topicID=3011.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3011.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3011.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgroveboardpostingrulesandpolicy">Board Posting Rules And Policy<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm22">Polls<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm20">Spoilers<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option value="thedruidsgrovequests">Quests<option value="thedruidsgrovedruidice